values:
Meh, but I can't be bothered to update. =P So here.





That's interesting... /= I'll stop now...

We actually had a lunch today, which was cool, I er, suppose. Though it sucked badly.  Nobody likes Grilled Cheese Sandwiches from a school. I mean yes, I enjoy them when they're made normally. Yet, the way most schools have them is disgusting. Like two pads of manufactured bread and some cheese which was only put in the microwave to melt. -shivers- x.x So, I just ate a salad, and a slice of cake. Yep, we have a lady who's soul job is to make deserts for us. I must say, she's quite good at it.  Then we had a break were we can walk around campus doing nothing. Which is odd... x.x

Meh... .... How does everyone have so many ideas about what to write? I have so many things I want to say, yet don't want to say them all in a rush. Plus nothing is interesting. =O I guess, I'm just boring. Ah, oh well. I'll try to make a long entry.  Though I can't promise a happy mood after the end of this sentence... 



-sigh- I actually took time to center that. Makes you wonder. Meh, my mother is going through some... Thing, I can't spell and don't really remember. Anyway, it makes her moody and ruthless according to the doctor.  -sigh- I thought she seemed a little more ticked than usually lately. x.x That's annoying in itself, though I know she can't help it. It still makes me mad. 

My parents are always mad at me... They never tell me if they're doing anything that they want me to join in on. No, they just do it and then when I have no idea it happened they get mad. AH! -_- Like just now, my dad walks down the hall in his bathing suit. ... So, I ask him if we're going swimming, his reply;

'No, we're getting out. Your mom and I have been in there the last hour.' I didn't even f'in' know my dad was home! -_- So, I closed my door and blasted up Green Day so I wouldn't be able to hear them. x.x I almost cried.  And I haven't cried for like six months, probably more...  Worse things have happened to me, but it just made me want to cry... Gah, I hate being expected to be telepathic... It makes me sad that they can yell at me for not spending a lot of time with them, then don't tell me when they do stuff together.

Gah, my mother has just in formed me that since our shower is messed up for some reason, we have to go to my grandparents to take them. Which means I might be forced to talk to them for a while. Crap.  Ah well, we're going to Hardees on the way. I'm gonna order the biggest f'in' thing on the menu for the bloody heck of it. ^^

I'll draw a line like above, when I leave...

-sigh- Now I don't know what to update about...

Is it wrong for a guy to feel lonely? There are times when I bloody want to shout to the world 'I love her!' However, I'm not that stupid. Plus, I know for a fact she likes someone else besides me, so heh, what's the point? -_- Is it wrong for me to love?  I answered in the last real update (ex-cluding the two about friends only) that I could trust no one with me life. I'm starting to think that not being able too, is bad for me emotionally. I just don't trust, I need to learn to trust. x.x When someone says they'll do something for me, I hardly ever believe them. I just don't trust people!  And I don't have many friends either... 

I'm the oddball out of most crowds.  .... All crowds.


Waven, please?

From now on this Journal is friends only. Sowwie, Em, but unless you get an LJ acount you won't be able to view... So, if you want to be added to my friends and aren't already, leave a comment! (As soon, as I post this I'm making a friends only post... ;) )

My life sucks. But I'll get to that after I rant about school... >_>

Twas a half day, today, which I suppose was a good thing, though I ended up getting no lunch until 2:00. <_< So, home room, I get the computer lab. This is awesome, what more could a person want then to have the computer lab as their home room classroom. ^^ I love having it as my home room. Mr. Schreck is interesting to talk to about computers as well, we had a talk about firewalls, and illegally sharing files. >_> Like I'm, or anyone else, going to listen to him and not illegally download stuff. It's not like the artists don't get enough money anyway. Besides, since speeding is a crime, we're all criminals. ^^

Anyway, so I have the computer lab for home room, so I'm set up for computer class first period. Which is cool. I don't like the way he makes us type though, I type almost 150+ graded words a minute when I can type my own way yet when I'm forced to type his way I only make about 80. >_> And 80 is teh sucks. I have to totally pwn everyone else in the class, 80 won't do that for me. Meh, but we didn't have any classes besides our core classes today because it was a half day and we were short on time.

After that, I have Mr. Hoth, math. >_> We're still doing plan math. I can't wait to get into algebra classes, which are actually fun. Even though algebra is easy, I've never understood why people think it's so hard. So hey, one more lonely year of boring math class then we get into algebra. I might be able to wait if I have a lot of luck and skill. >_> Mr. Hoth is odd. Not in a bad way, just odd. For instance, he made us memorize these dates;

June 4 - He started dating Ms. Allison.' What!? Who cares? Why does he think we want to hear anything about his tangled love life, much less memorize dates about it.
June 8 - His birthday.' Okay good, it's over the summer, I don't have to get him any sort of present for a birthday. Not that I would anyway/
June 18 - He went skydiving the first time.' Okay... >_> Who the heck cares about him going skydiving? I don't, and I can't believe we're being forced to memorize this. Not only that, but he 'hinted' it might come up on the quiz, that just happens to be on Friday.

His class isn't very wide, but it's pretty long, which is sort of interesting. Meh, to Science!!!

After that we go to Science. Something I should say, we have one period of Math, yet two in Science. Ah well, I'm not complaining about that. So, Mr. Gates teaches Science... He's room is cool, though we don't all have individual desks, we have tables, which I've never been found off. He has two snakes and a hamster! Plus he's interested in Tropical Systems. Which is really, really, really, really, really on going reallys for a while, cool! He's charting them. ^^

Anyway, off to something else.

Eh, I go back to school tomorrow. <_< I don't even have my schedule yet. So, tomorrow morning I'll have to wig it and go to the office getting my schedule the find all my classes by myself without knowing where any of my classes are. Not even my home room! -huffs- I don't really want to go back. No, I don't want to see my friends. So sue me, I'm a heartless moroon who doesn't care. I'm empty of emotion anyway. -huffs- Well there are a few people I want to see. 
Emily.
McKenzie.
Byung.
And thus ends the short list... Bah. >_>

At least I don't have to take Mr. Andrews this year, he's a liberal nazi. And bully for any of me fellow school students who honor him and will run off and tell him. Go ahead, I could care less if he knows I hate him. I hate him with every part of my being. So at least I'm lucky and won't have to take is stupid idiotic class! 

Ugh, now I'm in a flaming mood and have no one to flame. -takes it out on n00bs on Trio's-

Since I have nothing interesting to say, fear Blogthings!!!

Hmm, or not. >_> 

I'm going to post on Trio's

Today is Monday... I go back to school on Wednesday... Gah, this sucks so badly. I don't see a point in school. I mean most people would say it's to learn. Yet, I don't learn in school. I sit around doing nothing. Plsu, even if I do 'technically learn something, it's never anything I'll need to use after I get out of school. Which in itself is very annoying. I wonder what would happen if I went on strike... Probably nothing. I'm going to try out for soccer in the spring at Ben Lippen. I would try out for the Autumn season as well but I'm going to play for the Kershaw County Recreation Department. Just because my coach from last year is coming back and he's counting on me to come play for him. So I will, since I'm a really nice guy. It's not like were ever going to win at the Rec. Department. -sigh- Ah well... My mother is probably going to drag me off to buy stuff for school today. Which sucks, considering I don't even have my schedule. The rest of the school does, just not me. 

Gah! Now I'm in a bad mood. A bad mood with nothing to write about... I need to kick something. I should kick a rock. 

I got my computer back from the clutches of my evil parents today... ^^

Gah, screw this, I don't want to update. >_>

-carries it off to LJ in his mouth-

2. I will then tell you what song/movie reminds me of you.

6. I will tell you what animal you remind me of.
7. I'll then ask you something that I've always wondered about you.
8. If I do this for you, you must post this on your LJ.

It seems to be a default setting in most journals, yet the ability eludes mine... -sniff- I want to know what you peoples think!!! So, if you have any idea why people can't post in my journal, contact me and tell me how to fix it... If it works, I'll give you an Oreo Cookie. =')

You know you do, you kill me well.
You like it too, and I can tell.
You never stop until my final breath is gone.'

Spare me just three last words.
"I love you" is all she heard.
I'll wait for you, but I can't wait forever.

'-o.o-' Heh, 'Ohio is for Lovers' I like this song. It makes me smirk... And puts me in an evil plotting mood. Which is quite good as I have many evil plots to perform, and quite a few people on my 'PWNing List'. -noddles-
For instance, I have to pwn Dan. Even though he's my friend, I'm still going to pwn him. Meh... I'll think about that later...

I thought I was in a mood to right. Now, I can't think of anything much to say... -sigh- -wonders off to post on Trio's a little- ... .... ..... ...... -ish back-

Wheee! I shall talk about Trio's. Yesterday when McFluffeh (Rai), wanted a sig she asked Kara (Vi) for one. So, instead of making the actual sig, she was nice enough to allow her humble Totopuff (me. ^^) to create her a tag to go with it. So I did and was able to produce;

http://i15.photobucket.com/albums/a400/haxx0rz/RaiRai.gif

I waited until Kara had finished her siggy, so that I could see what would match the sig. This did, since her siggy was black and white. Then I was struck by a sudden inspiration. (It happens a lot, I know, don't be jealous. =D ) I decided to make tags for all the Trio's Elite peoples! So now we have;

Whee! Go Elite Peoples! ^^ Now I need to scout out a few more people to make a tag for. Like Waven... Hmm.

I am top posteher there. It's interesting to say the least, though, I've noticed an upswing in the owls from girls asking my character to be their characters boyfriend. It's odd, I mean do they not see Rai! -points at Rai- And do they honestly think I'd go out with someone who Don doesn't even know yet? Yesh! I have also noticed, that with more posts people add you to their AIM/MSN/YIM buddy lists just because you're popular. Then they show up going
'Uh... Who you?' because they randomly added all the top posters and don't even know who's who. So when I get someone like that I just say
'If you don't know who I am, I must not be very important to you, good bye.'
Then again, usually it doesn't work, for some odd reason... They're like;
'Uh... Did I get you off the Charmed site?' << What the heck is Charmed? O_o
Ack! it's even more annoying then when a girl asks me to allow my character to be their character's boyfriend.. -shivers- And that's scary in itself. 

Hmm, I guess I did have some stuff to say. However if you get sad (like normal people) don't read after this point. ^^ (Yes, I only say that because I know there is practically no chance anyone will stop here. ^^

(Oh, and I think I just fixed it so people can comment, meh-uh!! We just have to wait and see when I post this. =) )

My mother says I don't pay enough attention to my younger dog, Ceana (Kena) and that we might give her away to the Collie Rescue League... She suddenly pops this on me, I had no idea. Ceana was always playful with me, so I'm still not sure where she is getting this idea. But, I know I don't want them to give Ceana Bena away! No, that'd be very bad.... So, I've started walking her longer every day, and allowing her to sleep in my room... So meh. I hope we don't give her away. I'd never forgive my parents. They say she is too destructive... -sniff- And that being a collie she needs more attention. So, since I wub her!, I'm giving her ten times my normal amount off attention... I wub all my animals... -sniff- I don't want them to go anywhere.... 

Hugo came into my room today with a dead bird in his mouth... It was a female too... -grumbles- I know it's instinct for him to kill and bring food back to the pack.. But it stills is sad to see the poor bird. I mean, I don't blame the cats for killing it.... Meh.. -huffs-

Whee! That's it for this update. Now to see if you can comment...

My quizzes are saying each other are wrong. ^^ Well this has all been very interesting yet... On to words... Written by me.. O_O Wow.... Went to Gatlinburg last week... Had four girls tell me I was cute. Also, I noticed each one of them looked like they were 18. Meh... My parents had a file day with that. I suppose that's better than if they'd known about Aly... -shudders- And I quote; 'Hey, Tim, I'm wearing the new lipstick. Want to test the claim it won't come off?' That freaked me out... I'm not even good looking. -huffs- Maybe I'm in denial. Maybe I'm only say thing because I know McFluffeh is going to read this and be jealous. Maybe I'm only saying what I just said because I know it's not true. Maybe I'm crazy. Maybe the sky is blue... Oh wait... \= I guess it's to late for that. Anyway, they had a game room so my dad and I spent a long time playing billards... It was fun, and I must say I got a lot better. After the week was over, I'd actually beaten him a total of three times!!! Yes three! Yes I am proud of that... :P Maybe that is a bit sad but who cares? I was proud of it. I finally figured out how to hold the cue stick better... With my right hand farther back. I was so close to my left hand I didn't get much power in the hit. I still can't break well at all. But meh, my dad is happy to break for us and he never gets one in when he breaks... So, I shan't complain... Now anyway. They also had an air hockey machine. You know the little machine with the puck and two people hitting it back and forth tell seven points are scored by one of the two? It was fun. I uberly creamed anyone but my dad... My dad was about even to me in wins in losses. He only ever played me at Air Hockey anyway. The pool was interesting. This chick did nothing but look at me the whole time. How am I supposed to feel about this blond with a bikini looking at me none stop? Meh. ^^ maybe this is good. I'll have to see. We played tips with a small ball we bought at the local convenience store. That was very interesting. Then a bunch of girls came over in this really big family so my dad and mom got out and let all the kids play. But what was really cool was the father of one of them was big into computers. Who knew an adult computer geek would be impressed with my computer skills. He was running on some independent Internet browser I had never heard off. So, of course when I got home I had to research it. It looks good, but I still wub my Firefox. His browser ran in windows, not tabs. Plus it wasn't open source. So meh you couldn't edit it to your liking. However it was fun chatting with him. And -puts finger in front of mouth- we mentioned hacking a bit. Talked about the time in 2000-2001 AOL got hacked and completely shut down for three days.... I won't go into that because I'm most likely the only one who cares. Yet if you do, ask me and I'll talk about. (15 minute explanation. ^^) We were going to go to three dinner shows but meh we accidentally missed the third one. It was a Murder Mystery Dinner Party, and also the one we wanted to go to the most... So sad... -sniff- But the other two were interesting. The first was a play at the 'Sweet Phanny Adams Theater'. The play was called 'Once upon a trunk.' It was quite good, yet I didn't get any popcorn out of it... -sigh- Oh well, I might, if lucky get over it. The other being the Dixie Stampede. That was fun except for the fact that we were forced to sit on the southern Confederate side. -wanders off and grumbles- But once you got passed that the dinner was quite good. My dad got to go down during it and have a horseshoe match with a northerner.. -pokes- Yet it wasn't your ordinary horseshoes match! It was Dixie Stampede Style. Which in English means the horseshoes were toilet seats. w00t. But Dad one and got a supremely uber cool medal that I have sitting in my chair next to my bed. As I write this off all things... Whoa... Then came the day when I got to go home. w00t I finally was able to see my computer again. Which is a blessing in itself if you ask me. Trio's hadn't changed much. Apparently Britt has invoked a rule that Ben McFluffeh Adrian and I can't post in the SL none stop... So heartless. ^^ But I wub her all the same... McFluffeh is such a cool person. Evyone wubs her! Em is such a cool person. Evyone wubs her! Waven is such a cool person. Evyone wubs her! Ovi is such a stupid person. Everyone hates him! Yesterday was interesting, my mother's thirteen year old client, (uber hott. ^^) came over to spend some time at our house. Apparently she told my mom I was hott before she came, (she'd seen pictures of me...) O.O And then we went swimming... And she wore a bikini. Not only was she hott, but she makes Straight A's! ^^; I hope she can come back. :P Mom invited her back... Whee fun stuff. ^^ And she feel in love with my computer... -sniff- She needs to come back. -looks left and right- Then mother had to go to some meeting in Charleston and she left us alone in the pool. The subject reached our schools... Hmm, mine is full of preps and her's goths. Meh. What a lovely world we live in. I'd tell you her name.. But her being mother's client... I can't! Ha! -poketh- She wanted to play Test Drive on the Play Station, wall listening to Green Day in the background. So yes. -gets on knees- Come back!!! Hmm... And now I end this journal entry so I can read some before watching Who's Line is it Anyway. GO COLIN!!!! ^^

Buh.... I'm hopeless. I'm shy.... I'm scared.... No, terrified. Yet, I know if I had simply said something sooner I probably would've got the same response.... Yet, I still haven't.... I'm shy. \= 

Meh, camp was interesting... At times, at certain times it was horrible. \= But overall I had an enjoyable time. Two majors... It was an odd camp.
Out of Archery, Drama, Canoeing, Swimming, Riflary, and Outdoor Survival, I took Archery and Canoeing. Though I had to take canoeing, -sighs- it was mandatory for all those going on the canoe trip had to take that class....

Meh, the first part of the canoe trip stunk. \= The wind was blowing really fast, the opposite direction of the current and we were spinning in circles... Eventually it died down though and the last half I had fun... Sorta. I was worried though. About the two canoes the guide had to pull...

Hmm not much else to say about it. \= We rode four miles down the Congeree river. Oh my... O.O

Josiah (a person in my cabin) got a letter from a girl named Scarlette.... To which she signed 'Your secret 'admemearer''. That was humerous. And Lauren liked me... O.O 

Bah, I'm still shy.... I was going to last night, but I didn't... Good bye. \=
